Dialogue:
Will ye be needin' these
tools as well, milord?

Just tell me when
you've had enough, now.
I have five kids to feed!

My coin is as good
as the next man's!

Another order of lavender
from the Alchemists' Guild.

The Gridanians'll be none
too pleased 'bout that.

You simply must tell me
the recipe for this gruel!

You need me to call
one of the milkmaids
to help you with that?

I haven't worked so hard
since...since yesterday!

I claim this bed
in the name of...me!

Allow a man
a drink in peace.

We've no choice but to
put the poor beast down.

You ever seen
a red rooster?

Only after I've fried
one in dragon peppers.

But we were specifically
told the south shiel.

The sheep are so en-
gorged, they can't move!
What is that feed!?
What do you mean “wait”? I see three open tables!

How about you take a
crate for yourself?

Those dream flowers
cost us a fortune!

Call me that again
and this bucket goes
on your head.

Damned fowl keep
kicking over the paling...

Is it true what they
say about Sea Wolves?

I think he may have had
one too many sips.

I do not feel safe with
the imperials so close...

These were the only ones
to survive the Calamity.

Then I'll take ten bottles!
Price is no object!

Her husband had left.
I meant no harm, sir.
Not a sign of the blight!

This year's grapes'll
make a fine vintage.
Another round, wench! And put it on her tab!

Are you ready to discuss
the terms of our accord?

Red wine with yer meal?
Ye'll get what I give ye.

I cannot well concentrate
with ye gawpin' at me, now.

Why must the stable-
master insist we wear
these masks in this heat!?

Where in the seven hells
did those two run off to!?

These notched blades
couldn't even cut butter...

Gonna skin us some
fishbacks, we are.

Might ye 'ave some
jerked dodo? I've had
more'n me fill o' jellyfish.

Oh, what I wouldn't give
to be back on the Deep.

Never allow the fish-
backs the upper ground!

We must strike
while the iron is hot!

But strike them with
what? We remain
sorely undermanned!

Are the ballistas
ready for deployment?

Those contraptions do
us little good without
men to operate them!

I've an 'and free, if that
crate's too much fer ye.

I fear there won't be
enough to boil the pitch.

Aye, 'tis crawling with all
manner of dark spirits!

How'd ye fancy a bowl
o' stew with yer brown?

Ye look right ferm... Far...
Mill... Farmar... Aye, I
reckon I's seen ye afore.

The skies haven't been
kind to the harvest.

Ye need a woman as
me to watch yer backs!

Where's the bloody boat?
Me shoulder aches!
Well, she can certainly see you making an arse of yourself with that box.

You think she
can see us?

The tariff on ale has
risen 200 gil per barrel.

Might be time you got a
new pair o' spectacles.

Be careful with that
firesand, you fool!

The trunnion is warped
and the cascabel cracked!

What goes well with
warm sour ale? More ale.

I don't know why I
keep looking. I'm never
going to find it...

Just because you are
always right, doesn't
mean you are this time.

That was the greatest
quarter bell o' me life.

The problem is getting
the ale to Radz-at-Han
without it being drunk!

I've a mind to throw you
both in the brig to rot!

You 'ear? The cap'n
caught 'em ruttin' like
rabbits in 'is very bunk!

I've never seen a woman
as beautiful as you.

Sweet words comin' from
one who makes sour red.

From Ul'dah, ye say?
How'd ye roll that thing
across the strait, then!?

Faster! Harder!
Are you even listening!?

I'm thinkin' of layin' down
me sword after this next one.
Agh, my belly hurts somethin' fierce!
'Twas a dream so sweet... Now, it is a─hurk!─nightmare.
Will my raging innards know no peace!?
Yellow Moon. I've never seen a maid as fair...

Mummy, Mummy!
What was that thing?

Why, that was a...er...
Why don't you ask
your father, sweetling?

Cor! I ain't seen
nothin' like it!

I don't know what the
hells's going on, but
keep up the good work!

It's burning up the
quarter malm!

Gods, I think I'm
in love... \<sigh>

Die! Die! Die! Die a
thousand deaths an'
then die a thousand more!

I'm not one of them!
I swear it on what little
remains of my virtue!

What shall it be tonight,
Cap─ You're not the captain!

Forgive me, my lord!
I did not mean to offend!

Thank the Twelve!
This nightmare is over!

I shan't bite any more...
Just let me out!

Mother... Father... What
did I do to deserve this?

I don't think I can last
another night in the
Deckhands' Quarters...

Slit them between the
legs! Every last one of them!
Feel the true power of the Fist!

If the water were
any deeper, I'd drown!

My brain...
I think I boiled it.

Another word about my
hair, Midlander, and I'll
scalp you right here.

Can I interest you
ladies in a midnight dip?

The springs'll warm from
without, the wine within.

Care to join us?<If(PlayerParameter(4))><Else/> Or are
you not man enough
for the five of us?</If>

It appears we've been
discovered, ladies.

I can get twice as much
in Ul'dah for half the price!

Last stop for supplies
for ten score malms!

Five against one,
ye say? Cor!

This place has
certainly grown
lively of late.

These must all be moved
to the Find at once.

You want this aetheryte,
you have to get by me first!

Naught but
weeds, all of it.

The soft flesh under the
jaw. That's their weak spot.

Feels like I ate
a whole dragon.

What say you come
over to my bunk, squire?

I'd be warmer in
bed with a corpse.

The visor keeps my
eyes from freezing shut.

Well, you're obviously not
a giant. You may pass.

I say we dig
from the north face.

And I say we
dig from the south.

Never want for work
in a place as this.

Look at the masonwork!
The entire structure is
wrought from a single stone!

When the fog is thick, I
wouldn't wander too far.

The Gates are closed to
outsiders and unbelievers.

Too many adventurers
in Coerthas, I say.

They're almost as
bad as the dragons.

Three sacks of winter
wheat and a box of
rotting cabbage will not
see us through a siege.

Is there naught more to
life than fighting dragons?

All I see here is red
and white. The master
requested a rosé!

I've satisfied many a
woman in my fifty and
five summers.

This is why I don't hire
men! You only think with
that head 'twixt your legs!

Hah! Yer payin' me
with me own coin!

What I wouldn't give to
be down there sipping
rum from a coconut.

You hear a scream
from the palace?

Haven't missed yet.
(The cliff, that is.)

One, two... Nine, ten...
Forty-one, forty-two...

The dragons never
rest, nor shall we!

My arm... The damned
thing nearly bit it off!

The Fury has witnessed
your sacrifice. A place
in Her halls is secure.

Ten men lost their lives
when you broke the line!

My toes...they've all
grown black and cold.

Halt. State your─
Ah, another adventurer.

Quiet! You want the
knights to hear you!?

Pulled this knife
from her dead hands.
When in Coerthas, you must abide by our laws.

Do not dare question
our ways, unbeliever.

We can continue this no
longer. Think of your wife.

See that this axle is
greased before nightfall.

There goes another
heretic off Witchdrop.
If it isn't slaying dragons it's training to slay them.

Would you have us face
the Horde unprepared?

The weapons within are
those of the fallen.
Where did I place that copy of the Enchiridion?

Unbeliever lies, told to
make us forget our duty.

They say there's a place
in the south where the
water's warm as blood.

Quiet, both of you,
and concentrate!

An astrologian requires
ample time to ponder the
questions of the heavens.

I've had enough of the
stale bread, the stale ale,
and the stale company.

You have a problem
with my company?
Would you care for a drink?

All eight were cooked
alive in their armor...
What is it? Dragons? It's always dragons...

Took me half a lifetime
to find a woman what
could chop wood as good
as Linne.

But does the hat actually
increase your intelligence?

The Horde rarely
descends this far south.
Gigants and goobbues─
those are our bane.

The Horde will attack
again within the fortnight.

The See must be
made known of this!

You're a long way
from home, adventurer.

I do not envy the man
who must patrol the Gaze.

A bottle is missing!
Explain yourselves!

No mortal man could
survive such a drop.

Once the voidsent grab
hold, your soul is theirs.

Listen to him. Leave this
place and never return.

You need not fear.
This location is secure.
I am of the third shift.

Seventh shift is
always the worst.

We work in shifts to
ensure efficiency.

Another bell and my
shift will be over.

I'm with the eighth shift.
Or was it the ninth...?

I suppose you're
wondering just how
many shifts there are.

I try not to concern
myself with what
transpires within.

My shift number?
I don't know. Fourteen?

When my shift ends,
I'm going to drink
myself blind.

The man on fourteenth
was released from service.
I am the new fourteen!

Shifts come and go, like
the ebb and flow of the
tides. I am of the fifteenth.

Neither your life, nor
death, will be forgotten.

You'd think slayers of
dragons could catch a
bloody rat or two!

She's gone... And I
couldn't save her...

Come to warm
yourself, too, eh?

My new technique? I call
it, Eldritch Bane Thrust!

(Then why aren't you
down here with us? Hmph!)

They cannot keep
me down here!

You've always had
a way with words.
A gentleman is, rather than does!
I feel so cultured! I feel so refined!
The heathen's life is ours, brother.
Aye, another soul for Lord Ifrit.
As for the remainder of the shipment...
I shall see to it forthwith, sir.
I beg of you...save my comrades from those terrors.
What is scaredy one waiting for?
This one is ready for you!
Walking one will not leave here alive!
What is scaredy one waiting for?
This one is ready for you!
Walking one will not leave here alive!
To others this is a patty of ground meat. To me this is a work of art.
Godsdammit, man! I know you can work faster than that!
Ick! This one is all sticky!
You are not what I expected...
These ones must protect these ones' home!
Walking one is strong one! This one will leave the rest to strong one!
Stupid ones will never see it coming. Tee hee!
These ones are smart ones, oh yes.
You there, on your feet! These paving stones aren't going to lay themselves!
For gods' sakes, do I have to do everything myself!?

Gods help me, I'm
starting to see paving
stones in my dreams...
Bleedin' waste of me sword arm...
I don't see anything. Do you?
Only one way to find out...

Here for training,
I take it?

Go right on in.
Don't be shy!

Not losing your
nerve, I hope?

Me infirm grandma
hits harder than ye!
To the victor go the spoils!
Ah, fresh meat for the grinder.

The meek shall inherit
a hole in the ground!

Oh, gods, what've I
gotten myself into...

Are you fighting or farting!?
The spectators are like to
laugh themselves to death!

If you show your fear,
you've already lost.

What the hells are you
waiting for? The cavalry!?

If I can catch
them unawares...

The eye of the coeurl!
Show it to me!
How do you like my pets? Not too playful for you, I hope?

Naught is nobler
than single combat
between gladiators.

Taking a spear to the
gut is the worst...

A gladiator must
know how to pierce
every defense!

Without endurance, a
gladiator has nothing.

Oh, gods, make it end... I've
got nothin' left to bring up...

Why work when sleep
feels so good? Rest...
Slumber... Zzz...
My only wishhh is to catch a fishhh─they're so juicy-sssweet!
Read the flow of the currentsss...
You come here why? Yes, yes, to die!
I'll boil you─cook you, simmer you, boil you!
Paws off, you brutes─you beasts, you savages, you brutes!
You should be on your guard against mischief!
